//written in java

/*Implement a simple program in Main.java that greets the user.
• The program receives an argument, which should be an integer (e.g., 9). This should represent a time (full hour, values ​​1 to 24).
• Depending on the time, different greetings should be written to the console for the user. (e.g., "Good morning" if the time is between 6 and 10.)
• There should be at least three different greetings.
• There should be a greeting for each time.
• An invalid input (e.g., 25, 0, or -1) should output a corresponding message to the console. */

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args){
		
		int a = Integer.parseInt(args[0]);
		
		
		if(a>=6 && a<=12){
			System.out.println("Guten Morgen!!");
	} else if (a>12 && a<18){
		System.out.println("Guten Nachmittag!!");
	} else if (a>=18 && a<=22){
		System.out.println("Guten Abend oder Gute Nacht!!");
	} else if (a>22 || a<6){
		System.out.println("Es ist Ruhezeit!!");
	} else {
		System.out.println("Geben Sie bitte gültige Uhrzeit ein!!");
	}
		
			
    }
}
